The New York Liberty remembered what Tamika

article.headline: Robinson scores season-high 24 to lead Liberty

images.name: Robinson, Crystal 020625 inline
images.caption: New York's Crystal Robinson goes up for two of her season-high 24 points.

article.linkText: New York controls Catchings to dominate Indiana
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Liberty remembered what Tamika
Catchings did the last time the team met the Indiana Fever.

<photo1>

	   New York made sure there wasn't a repeat performance.

	   Crystal Robinson scored a season-high 24 points as the Liberty
routed the Fever 74-55 and shut down Catchings to snap a three-game
losing streak Tuesday night.

	   ''We kept reading about what a great player Catchings was,''
Liberty coach Richie Adubato said. ''We were determined we could
stop her with our defense.''

	   Catchings, second in the WNBA with 18.8 points a game, had 32
points and 14 rebounds in Indiana's 71-62 victory over New York on
June 8. This time, Catchings had just 12 points.

	   ''Vickie Johnson did a marvelous job on her,'' Adubato said.
''She's a very tough competitor.''

	   Robinson shot 9-for-12 from the field, including 6-for-9 from
3-point range, for the Liberty (8-6). Becky Hammon added 12 points
and Teresa Weatherspoon had six points and a game-high 10 assists
for New York, which led 36-19 at halftime.

	   ''I saw (Robinson) had the hot hand, and I like to spoon-feed
people and I made sure I fed her the ball,'' Weatherspoon said.
''You have to get her the ball when she wants it because she knows
when she's on fire.''

	   Robinson went into the game focused on stopping Catchings, who
shot 3-for-10 from the field.

	   ''I wanted to keep her off the boards,'' Robinson said.
''Tonight, I was able to get a lot more transition baskets, thanks
to Spoon. We executed well.''

	   Bridget Pettis came off the bench to lead the Fever (5-7) with
13 points.

	   ''We had a real bad shooting night,'' Indiana coach Nell Fortner
said. ''We've got to defend better than we did tonight.''

	   The victory was the Liberty's fourth in a row over the Fever,
and seventh in eight meetings as New York opened a five-game
homestand.

	   ''Now that the three-game losing streak is behind us, we have to
play like this the rest of the way,'' Weatherspoon said.

	   Tari Phillips scored three points as New York jumped out to a
7-0 lead at 3:37 into the game. Pettis cut it to 9-5 at 11:27, but
the Liberty went on a 12-1 run behind a pair of 3-pointers by
Robinson to make it 21-6 at 18:23.

	   Indiana, which has lost five of six, never got closer than 24-16
in the half on two free throws by Catchings with 4:09 remaining.
Robinson made two more 3s as the Liberty went 12-3 the rest of the
half.

	   After Catchings opened the second-half scoring, the Liberty got
two layups by Vickie Johnson and scored 10 consecutive points to
turn it into a rout at 46-21 -- New York's largest lead -- at 16:35.


	   Rita Williams made a layup to bring Indiana to 16 down at 61-45
with 5:28 left, but that was as close as the Fever could get.

	   The Liberty shot 8-for-14 from 3-point range, but the Fever were
just 3-for-14.

	   ''We had some good looks, but we couldn't knock them down
early,'' Fortner said. ''That affected our confidence. We gave up
too many uncontested 3s.''
